						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Pṛithivī-Vallabha Dēvakumāra,</hi> son of king <hi rend="bold">Mahādēva,</hi> gave 50 cows for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Agastyēśvara. The donor bears the title of the Eastern Chāḷukyas.</p>						

